Per docs/schema/02-traits.md T-1 (owner-approved): origin is the single
source of truth for robot identity. Trait-level robot-* fields are
duplicates that drift from origin and clutter the modifier registry.

Audit before this patch:
  - trait.modifiers.robotRules:     read in 0 places (dead).
  - trait.modifiers.robotType:      read in 0 places (dead).
  - trait.modifiers.robotBodyPlan:  read in 3 places — but origin.bodyPlan
                                    is already populated for ALL 5 robot
                                    origins, so the trait copy was just
                                    a legacy fallback.
  - trait.modifiers.isRobot:        already removed in a previous pass;
                                    only mentioned in stale comments.

Data (data/traits/traits.json), 3 traits cleaned:
  - protectron-protect-or-destroy:  remove robotRules block.
  - assaultron-designed-for-frontline: remove robotRules block.
  - misterhandy-robot-mr-handy:     remove robotType + robotBodyPlan +
                                    robotRules.

About robotRules specifically (owner's call):
  Fields like canEquipStandardArmor/canEquipPowerArmor will be re-modeled
  through origin.armorRules once docs/schema/01b is closed (open C/D/E).
  Fields like canSelfUseConsumables/canUseConsumablesOnOthers had no
  readers and would have stayed as 'true'-by-default anyway — re-introduce
  only with a real implementation + explicit deviation in data. Storing
  'true for everyone' just bloats the data and obscures whether the value
  is a deliberate rule or copy-paste.

Code:
  - domain/bodyplan.js #resolveBodyPlan:
      drop legacy fallback . Single source
      of truth is origin.bodyPlan; defensive ROBOT_ORIGIN_TO_PLAN keeps
      working for old saves without origin.bodyPlan.

  - components/screens/WeaponsAndArmorScreen/WeaponsAndArmorScreen.js:
      findRobotBodyUpgrade(...) now reads origin?.bodyPlan instead of
      trait?.modifiers?.robotBodyPlan. origin is already in scope.

  - components/screens/InventoryScreen/InventoryScreen.js:
      robotBodyPlan now resolves to origin?.bodyPlan first; the
      equippedRobotBodyPart?.robotBodyPlan fallback stays for in-flight
      body-swap UX. origin is already in scope.

Verified: bodyplan.js syntax OK; data/traits/traits.json still valid JSON;
no readers of trait.modifiers.robotBodyPlan/robotType/robotRules outside
comments.
